theorem interior_closure_idempotent_seven {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior (closure (interior A)))))))) =
      interior (closure A) := by
  simp [Topology.interior_closure_idempotent]

theorem closure_interior_union_three_subset {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B C : Set X} :
    closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) ∪ closure (interior C) ⊆
      closure (interior (A ∪ B ∪ C)) := by
  intro x hx
  -- Break the three‐fold union into cases.
  cases hx with
  | inl hAB =>
      -- Case 1: `x ∈ closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B)`
      -- First, reduce to the two‐set statement already available.
      have hxAB : x ∈ closure (interior (A ∪ B)) := by
        have hsub :
            closure (interior A) ∪ closure (interior B) ⊆
              closure (interior (A ∪ B)) :=
          Topology.closure_interior_union_subset (X := X) (A := A) (B := B)
        exact hsub hAB
      -- Enlarge once more to incorporate `C`.
      have hsubset :
          closure (interior (A ∪ B)) ⊆
            closure (interior (A ∪ B ∪ C)) := by
        -- `interior` is monotone, so it suffices to show the same for the sets
        -- inside the `interior`.
        have hinner :
            (interior (A ∪ B) : Set X) ⊆ interior (A ∪ B ∪ C) := by
          have hAB_subset : (A ∪ B : Set X) ⊆ A ∪ B ∪ C :=
            Set.subset_union_left
          exact interior_mono hAB_subset
        exact closure_mono hinner
      exact hsubset hxAB
  | inr hC =>
      -- Case 2: `x ∈ closure (interior C)`
      have hsubset :
          closure (interior C) ⊆
            closure (interior (A ∪ B ∪ C)) := by
        -- As above, reduce the claim to one about the sets inside `interior`.
        have hinner :
            (interior C : Set X) ⊆ interior (A ∪ B ∪ C) := by
          have hC_subset : (C : Set X) ⊆ (A ∪ B) ∪ C :=
            Set.subset_union_right (A ∪ B) C
          -- Combine the two obvious inclusions:
          -- `interior C ⊆ C` and `C ⊆ A ∪ B ∪ C`.
          exact interior_mono (Set.Subset.trans interior_subset hC_subset)
        exact closure_mono hinner
      exact hsubset hC

theorem interior_closure_subset_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : Set X) :
    interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A := by
  simpa using (interior_subset : interior (closure A) ⊆ closure A)
